  <h3 class="ui header">
    <i class="settings icon"></i>
    Configuring your Okta org
  </h3>
  <p>
    If you don't
    <a href="https://www.okta.com/developer/signup/">
      have an Okta org
    </a>
    or haven't
    <a href="https://help.okta.com/en/prev/Content/Topics/Apps/Apps_App_Integration_Wizard.htm?Highlight=openid%20connect#OIDCWizard">
      set up an OIDC app
    </a>
    yet,
    you can use the included mock Okta server for quick testing:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="bash"># Start the mock-okta server on http://127.0.0.1:{{config.mockOkta.port}}
[samples]$ npm run mock-okta

  </code></pre>

  <p>
    To test these samples against your own Okta org and OIDC app, update
    the following settings in <strong>.samples.config.json</strong> and restart
    your server:
  </p>
  <table class="ui table compact collapsing">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Setting</th>
        <th>Value</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>oktaSample.oidc.oktaUrl</td>
        <td>The base url for your okta org, i.e. https://{yourOktaDomain}.com</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>oktaSample.oidc.issuer</td>
        <td>The url for your default okta authorization server, i.e. https://{yourOktaDomain}.com/oauth2/default</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>oktaSample.oidc.clientId</td>
        <td>
          The clientId for your OIDC app.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>oktaSample.oidc.clientSecret</td>
        <td>The clientSecret for your OIDC app</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="ui modal" data-se="overview-modal">
    <i class="close icon"></i>
    <div class="header">
      Building a New Frontend Sample
    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <p>
        This is a generated sample app built in Vanilla Javascript - it contains
        the markup and logic you'll need to build your own sample.
      </p>
      <strong>What you need to do:</strong>
      <div class="ui list">
        <div class="item">
          <i class="code icon"></i>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="header">
              Replace the vanilla JS files in the app/ directory with code for
              your frontend framework.
            </div>
            <div class="description">
              <div class="ui bulleted list">
                <div class="item">
                  The sample renders to the right hand column - you should not
                  need to modify the doc templates.
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                  See the
                  <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/okta/samples-js-angular-1/tree/master/app">
                    Angular 1 Sample
                  </a>
                  for an example of how to do this.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <i class="terminal icon"></i>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="header">
              Run "npm test" to verify that you've implemented the views correctly.
            </div>
            <div class="description">
              This is a set of end-to-end selenium tests that cover the scenarios
              we care about.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <i class="hand peace icon"></i>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="header">
              Once you've passed the tests, you're done! Well, almost.
            </div>
            <div class="description">
              Follow the guidelines to
              <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/okta/generator-samples#publishing-your-samples">
                publish your sample
              </a>.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="actions">
      <div class="ui positive right labeled icon button" data-se="overview-modal-btn">
        Okay, I'm ready to begin!
        <i class="checkmark icon"></i>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
        <div class="column seven wide sample-col right floated">
          <div class="ui orange labels">
            <div class="ui label" data-tooltip="Backend" data-inverted="" data-position="bottom center">
              {{#config.server.environment}}
                {{#config.server.framework}}
                  {{config.server.framework}}
                  <div class="detail">{{config.server.environment}}</div>
                {{/config.server.framework}}
                {{^config.server.framework}}
                  {{config.server.environment}}
                {{/config.server.framework}}
              {{/config.server.environment}}
              {{^config.server.environment}}
                Express <div class="detail">NodeJS</div>
              {{/config.server.environment}}
            </div>
            <div class="ui label" data-tooltip="Frontend" data-inverted="" data-position="bottom center">
              <span id="frontend-framework">
                <span data-se="js-loading" class="ui active inline loader mini inverted"></span>
              </span>
              <div class="detail" id="frontend-environment"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="app-container">
            <div id="default-app-text">&lbrace;&lbrace; Samples render here &rbrace;&rbrace;</div>
          </div>
        </div>
